  "welcome": {
    "greeting": "Hola, {{name}}",
    "pageTitle": "¡Bienvenido a OIUEEI!",
    "description": "OIUEEI es una aplicación web de código abierto que permite a las personas compartir sus pertenencias con amigos y otras personas. Los usuarios pueden crear colecciones (listas de deseos, listas de regalos, artículos en venta) y compartirlas con amigos que pueden reservar artículos o hacer preguntas.",
    "createCollection": "Crear colección",
    "editProfile": "Editar perfil",
    "whoUsesTitle": "¿Quién usa OIUEEI?",
    "personaLalaTitle": "Lala — The Sabbatical-Taker.",
    "personaLalaBody": "She's off. Imminently. Leaving behind a flat full of excellent taste and absolutely no desire to haggle. A tenner each, cash, you collect. Simple as that — rather like Lala herself.",
    "personaLeleTitle": "Lele — The Baker.",
    "personaLeleBody": "She rises at 5am voluntarily and considers it a treat. Her cakes are architectural achievements; her pistachio buns, frankly, deserve a Michelin star of their own. Natural ingredients only — because your birthday deserves better than a label you can't pronounce.",
    "personaLiliTitle": "Lili — The Lender.",
    "personaLiliBody": "Proof that sharing is indeed caring, and that most home projects require a drill you'll use exactly once. Lili has it. Lili will lend it. Lili only asks that you return it clean. Is that really so much to ask?",
    "personaLoloTitle": "Lolo — The Book Lover.",
    "personaLoloBody": "She believes every great novel deserves rain, a blanket, and spirited conversation over tea. Her club is a haven for those who like their heroes tortured and their moors windswept. One cannot simply read Wuthering Heights. One must survive it together.",
    "personaLuluTitle": "Lulu — The Phantom Curator.",
    "personaLuluBody": "Nobody quite knows where she finds these things. Nobody quite knows where she goes. Her shelf updates weekly with objects that have lived a life — fondue sets, leather cases, silent exercise bikes — all deserving a second chapter. Everything here has a past. Whether you ask about it is entirely up to you."
  },
